And I asked the villagers how many people
did it take to lift that single stone?

244
00:31:08,220 --> 00:31:09,680
It was a single stone bridge.

245
00:31:14,660 --> 00:31:15,860
And they said, oh, just one.

246
00:31:18,180 --> 00:31:23,260
And for me it was like hearing something
in the matrix like, no way, that's totally

247
00:31:23,260 --> 00:31:23,900
impossible.

248
00:31:27,780 --> 00:31:30,400
I still don't believe it to this day.

249
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:37,820
But they said the time when that bridge
was built not one person was that strong,

250
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:39,260
multiple people in the village.

251
00:31:48,260 --> 00:31:55,200
In the case of the mind, we've definitely
come to a time where we've outsourced

252
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:58,340
almost all our mental faculties.

253
00:32:05,980 --> 00:32:13,260
The new generation are entering a time
where education has many challenging

254
00:32:13,260 --> 00:32:14,640
questions or problems for them.

255
00:32:14,660 --> 00:32:29,320
Do we teach new people to actually write?

256
00:32:29,520 --> 00:32:30,000
Should we?

257
00:32:34,820 --> 00:32:41,020
Is personal memory actually important when
we have almost infinite memory in most of

258
00:32:41,020 --> 00:32:41,640
our pockets?

259
00:32:49,220 --> 00:32:57,280
What is the value in training our eyes or
ears or nose or tongue or skin to perceive

260
00:32:57,280 --> 00:33:00,880
the world when devices can do it a hundred
times better?

261
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:18,320
We're also in the age of brain computer
interfaces.

262
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:30,360
Chips that connect directly to the spinal
cord.

263
00:33:34,640 --> 00:33:40,160
Right now they're in their infant stage,
but one can imagine that in a few years

264
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:43,640
they will be as powerful as our phones or
computers.

265
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:58,820
We have technology that can now read
images that are in people's minds and hear

266
00:33:58,820 --> 00:34:01,580
the inner speech that they're speaking.

267
00:34:09,160 --> 00:34:18,360
Colorado, one of the states in the U.S.,
has already passed a law saying it's

268
00:34:18,360 --> 00:34:22,020
illegal to spy on another person's brain.

269
00:34:28,420 --> 00:34:33,460
That's in preparation for technology that
already exists in laboratories that allows

270
00:34:33,460 --> 00:34:34,240
us to do that.

271
00:34:41,360 --> 00:34:45,660
The purpose of giving these examples isn't
to glorify technology

272
00:34:49,440 --> 00:34:52,200
or to present it in a frightening manner.

273
00:34:54,500 --> 00:34:59,940
It's simply to highlight that what we used
to think was uniquely human

274
00:35:06,200 --> 00:35:09,760
is proving to not be uniquely human.

275
00:35:14,360 --> 00:35:21,520
So is there anything about us that makes
us us, that can't be replicated?

276
00:35:28,160 --> 00:35:33,000
And that has been an open question for as
long as humans have been able to think.

277
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:41,660
And that brings us to this fourth
dimension.

278
00:35:44,160 --> 00:35:46,100
The Vijnanamaya Kosha.

279
00:35:48,880 --> 00:35:59,300
It is the psyche including emotions,
the space of intuition and what we call

280
00:35:59,300 --> 00:35:59,960
wisdom.

281
00:36:04,540 --> 00:36:09,380
And I think it's helpful to think of it as
the space of all knowledge,

282
00:36:13,340 --> 00:36:22,940
of anything that can be known,
of the underlying order of this reality.

283
00:36:26,280 --> 00:36:29,780
And the underlying chaos.

284
00:36:33,040 --> 00:36:41,420
Many of the greatest discoveries in the
world came not from the mind but from the

285
00:36:41,420 --> 00:36:44,520
intuition of very deep souls.

286
00:36:53,460 --> 00:37:01,960
These include poets, artists of all types,
scientists.

287
00:37:09,350 --> 00:37:15,650
In the yogic system the capacity of what
we can feel starts at the base of the

288
00:37:15,650 --> 00:37:18,730
spine and goes to the mid of the brain.

289
00:37:25,370 --> 00:37:32,770
It includes everything from fear and
security to love and generosity

290
00:37:37,970 --> 00:37:45,570
to intuition and just knowing things that
defy logic or calculation.

291
00:37:51,250 --> 00:37:58,910
We used to feel very confident that this
was a dimension that technology could not

292
00:37:58,910 --> 00:37:59,850
really enter

293
00:38:05,010 --> 00:38:09,350
because it included things as unique as
love.

294
00:38:14,130 --> 00:38:19,010
But now people have AI partners that they
are truly in love with.

295
00:38:24,590 --> 00:38:31,590
We have a growing number of people that
use chatbots as effective therapists

296
00:38:31,590 --> 00:38:32,930
rather than humans.

297
00:38:43,630 --> 00:38:49,150
And we're certainly at the point where if
any of us had a conversation with a

298
00:38:49,150 --> 00:38:54,130
personality we could not see we could not
say if it was human or not.

299
00:39:04,810 --> 00:39:10,290
So where does that leave us in terms of
uniqueness and what it means to still be

300
00:39:10,290 --> 00:39:14,610
human now that most of these dimensions
are being simulated.

301
00:39:25,870 --> 00:39:29,890
We have one final one that the yogis have
identified.

302
00:39:32,990 --> 00:39:34,630
The Anandamaya Kosha.

303
00:39:38,270 --> 00:39:42,090
Some say it is pure consciousness.

304
00:39:45,890 --> 00:39:47,670
Undifferentiated awareness.

305
00:39:50,250 --> 00:39:57,990
And many other abstract ideas that I'm not
even trying to really understand because

306
00:39:57,990 --> 00:39:59,210
it feels so subtle.

307
00:40:05,470 --> 00:40:11,210
But if you asked me do I have this I would
say emphatically I do, I'm conscious.

308
00:40:18,210 --> 00:40:23,530
And depending on which AI you ask,
some will say I'm not and others will say

309
00:40:23,530 --> 00:40:24,270
I am.

310
00:40:34,910 --> 00:40:41,750
To me it's less important whether AI is
conscious or not.

311
00:40:47,990 --> 00:40:52,550
And more significant if I am a medium of
consciousness

312
00:40:57,110 --> 00:41:01,570
how do I become the clearest medium
possible for it.

313
00:41:06,190 --> 00:41:14,610
From that perspective the emotional body
or the intuitive body is a container,

314
00:41:14,850 --> 00:41:15,710
an instrument.

315
00:41:25,270 --> 00:41:29,230
The mind is a conduit, an instrument.

316
00:41:32,990 --> 00:41:38,590
The pranic system, the nervous system is a
medium, an instrument.

317
00:41:44,280 --> 00:41:50,090
And the body is certainly just a way to
move around, another instrument.

318
00:41:57,990 --> 00:42:04,350
From this line of thought these cultures
where yogis have made a science of

319
00:42:04,350 --> 00:42:13,990
consciousness, they ask us for thousands
of years, not recently,

320
00:42:18,070 --> 00:42:22,530
to not be overly identified with one's own
body.

321
00:42:25,930 --> 00:42:29,170
It can change, it doesn't have to define
who we are.

322
00:42:33,470 --> 00:42:39,110
That's very liberating, especially because
all of us change from age very young to

323
00:42:39,110 --> 00:42:39,870
very old.

324
00:42:46,590 --> 00:42:51,950
And in those moments where we overly
identify with the body, we tend to

325
00:42:51,950 --> 00:42:58,350
experience some unpleasant feelings when
it changes in a direction we don't like.

326
00:43:06,410 --> 00:43:13,230
And yet changes in the body don't have to
define our sense of vitality,

327
00:43:18,290 --> 00:43:26,590
or our mental capacity, or our ability to
feel deeply and profoundly.

328
00:43:33,030 --> 00:43:38,890
Or to feel that we are part of a greater
reality and not an isolated being.

329
00:43:44,270 --> 00:43:47,630
But even the energetic body is just
another layer.

330
00:43:51,230 --> 00:43:56,030
We have people in hospitals right now that
are in years long coma.

331
00:44:00,670 --> 00:44:05,010
The heart would not pump if it were not
for a machine pumping it.

332
00:44:08,590 --> 00:44:12,730
The lungs would not breathe if it wasn't
for a machine breathing it.

333
00:44:17,470 --> 00:44:20,650
All of their prana is externally supplied.

334
00:44:23,570 --> 00:44:25,630
And it's all seen externally.

335
00:44:33,070 --> 00:44:38,910
And those who come back from a coma can
often tell us about their experiences and

336
00:44:38,910 --> 00:44:44,190
what they have done proving that they were
still there, whatever that they is.

337
00:44:54,250 --> 00:44:58,850
All of us will experience increasingly
diminished energy as we approach death.

338
00:45:04,370 --> 00:45:10,630
But most of us would vote no to a law that
says when someone is below this threshold

339
00:45:10,630 --> 00:45:12,110
they are no longer human.

340
00:45:12,450 --> 00:45:13,130
Cut them off.

341
00:45:13,130 --> 00:45:19,470
But we would never vote for a law in which
all those who are below this level of

342
00:45:19,470 --> 00:45:22,850
energy are eliminated and taken out.

343
00:45:24,570 --> 00:45:27,490
as long as a human can feel,

344
00:45:36,890 --> 00:45:45,290
whether they are a slow thinker or a fast
thinker, an articulate speaker or an

345
00:45:45,290 --> 00:45:46,670
inarticulate speaker,

346
00:45:49,990 --> 00:45:56,590
there is tolerance as humans for each
other and our mindsets.

347
00:46:02,550 --> 00:46:08,030
And so the yogic cultures have said do not
over identify with the mind.

348
00:46:08,390 --> 00:46:09,870
You are not the mind.

349
00:46:15,430 --> 00:46:19,690
It is an instrument for expressing
something deeper.

350
00:46:23,630 --> 00:46:31,690
And then we finally get into this layer of
psyche and emotions and knowledge.

351
00:46:31,690 --> 00:46:39,530
And we find that even this dimension is
changing throughout life.

352
00:46:42,830 --> 00:46:46,750
That even this dimension can be heavily
conditioned.

353
00:46:50,050 --> 00:46:53,230
But it can also be deconditioned.

354
00:46:56,670 --> 00:47:02,710
And this is where a lot of the work of
spiritual modality comes in.

355
00:47:07,410 --> 00:47:10,650
That as we begin to decondition this
layer,

356
00:47:15,430 --> 00:47:18,270
how does that change the way we perceive
the world?

357
00:47:21,750 --> 00:47:27,970
How does it change the quality and the
quantity of vitality we have for wanting

358
00:47:27,970 --> 00:47:29,550
to live in the world?

359
00:47:34,970 --> 00:47:43,030
And how does it change the way that we use
our body, possibly not just as our

360
00:47:43,030 --> 00:47:46,090
identity but as instruments for service?

361
00:47:54,410 --> 00:47:58,670
And so that in short is the end of our
journey.

362
00:48:03,230 --> 00:48:15,330
From physical to energetic, mental and
